#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:477
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Note that I originally developed this game under &Windows; with Borland C+"
#| "+ and WinG. I ported it to &Java; before converting back to C++ and "
#| "&kde;. At the beginning I used French or a mix of French and English to "
#| "name the identifiers (classnames, methods, members, &etc;). I also used "
#| "French for the comments. When I decided to distribute this game, I "
#| "decided to convert all to english... but I am clearly not a native "
#| "English speaker: please suggest or make and submit corrections, to the "
#| "code comments or to this documentation"
msgid ""
"Note that I originally developed this game under &Windows; with "
"<application>Borland C++</application> and <application>WinG</application>. "
"I ported it to &Java; before converting back to C++ and &kde;. At the "
"beginning I used French or a mix of French and English to name the "
"identifiers (classnames, methods, members, &etc;). I also used French for "
"the comments. When I decided to distribute this game, I decided to convert "
"all to english... but I am clearly not a native English speaker: please "
"suggest or make and submit corrections, to the code comments or to this "
"documentation."
msgstr ""
"Teña en conta que este xogo desenvolvino orixinalmente en &Windows; con "
"Borland C++ e WinG. Porteino a &Java; antes de convertelo de novo en C++ e "
"&kde;. No comezo empreguei francés ou unha mestura de francés e inglés para "
"os nomes dos identificadores (nomes de clases, métodos, membros, &etc;). "
"Tamén empreguei o francés para os comentarios. Cando decidín distribuír este "
"xogo decidín convertelo todo a inglés… pero é obvio que non son falante "
"nativo de inglés: suxire ou crea e remite correccións aos comentarios do "
"código ou a esta documentación. [Nota do tradutor ao galego: o mesmo podes "
"facer co meu traballo]."

